D.q[5648] = "Greetings. The evil grows stronger and stronger within you. You make me proud!\nWhy have you come?";
D.q[7813] = "Sioux Staurme arrived safely? Thank you, I feel much better knowing that.\nCan you accompany her brother Jauni now? He\'s getting a little impatient and has started annoying Grimmben, I\'m a little worried those two will actually come to blows.";
D.q[7814] = "That Jauni Staurme is really starting to get on my nerves. If his sister hadn\'t asked me to watch over him, I\'d willingly let him be devoured by Sabredons.";
D.q[2620] = "Grrrump.... grumph\n*He quickly tells you he doesn\'t know a thing.*";
D.q[7817] = "During your absence, Red tried to convince me to accompany you, but I refused. If Red is left alone here, he might be attacked, but I have less to fear from the forest creatures than him. Go with him and come get me afterwards.";
D.q[4736] = "Guards! GUARDS!!!";
D.q[4396] = "Excellent work. I knew I could trust you. I don\'t think anybody noticed you were gone, but the traitor must be keeping his head down, so you\'ll have to keep your wits about you. I\'m counting on you to wrap this investigation up, after all, it\'s your honour that\'s at stake.";
D.q[1079] = "Yes you\'re right! I just don\'t feel like going on break right now. Well... I... you know... I\'m in love, that\'s why. Sorry, I can\'t tell you any more.";
D.q[739] = "My Tabi is not feeling very well at the moment. \nA good meal would do him good. His favourite dish consists of crushing 4 different Blop Flowers.\nCome on #1, a little exercise against Blops will do you good!";
D.q[1577] = "Glad to see you again, Atall Tramston! But that was not very smart of you to get caught like that!";
D.q[7820] = "I can see that they are all safe, I\'m not senile.\nThank you for getting them out of this bloody mess. It\'s nice to be able count on people without being betrayed. I hope you don\'t end up like that wretched Count Harebourg.";
D.q[3878] = "Yes, that\'s what we need...However, I didn\'t understand whether Yse Vewybad wants to kill Rogues or hire them. Maybe you\'ll understand better... We\'ll just have to ask Yse.";
D.q[7821] = "You don\'t look too excited, so I have something to offer you.\nMy buddies and I set off on a Mama Pingwin hunt when Gerard disappeared. He stopped behind a tree to empty his bladder and we never saw him again. It was there one minute, and POOF! gone the next.\nHow would you feel about going to look for him?";
D.q[7822] = "Awesome. Begin by asking Damar, the chief fisherman. With a little luck, he\'ll have seen him.";
D.q[60] = "Oh, how I\'m suffering, but it\'s so delectable. Hmm, my wings hurt, I spent the whole night flogging them...";
D.q[5628] = "*Thinks* I\'m the greatest.\n*Thinks* I\'m the greatest.\n*Thinks* I\'m the greatest.\n*Thinks* I\'m the greatest.";
D.q[7829] = "You\'re not really looking for that drunkard, are you?\nHe passed by a few days ago, completely drunk. He was a little frisky and he staggered up close with his wandering hands, and I gave him what for, believe me.\nHe left, folded up double, in the direction of the Pingwin Cavern.";
D.q[5304] = "";
D.q[7855] = "Excellent news. You\'ve got nothing to do I guess, so you can deliver my Icefish. Take them to Aurora Borealis, north of the lake, Bambelle, who looks after the sawmill to the south, and Clarisse Tocrate, the village fishmonger.\nI\'ll lend you Pingwobble that\'s specially trained for transporting Icefish. It swallows the amount of Icefish required, and once at his destination, he regurgitates the delivery intact. I admit that it\'s not a flawless plan because his digestive system is activated thirty minutes after he\'s fed, so it\'s in your best interests to hurry.";
D.q[7865] = "We are planning to renovate a section of the village covered with ice and dig new houses in the ice itself. We also plan to build a huge hotel, totally dug out of and carved from the ice. It\'s a long project but we are determined to see it through to the end.\nI already bought a drill from the fishermen that our handyman Mac Gayver is currently fixing. Unfortunately, we\'re suffering from a shortage of raw materials and our tools are old and worn, which considerably slows the project\'s progress. But don\'t worry, we\'re not throwing in the towel just yet.";
D.q[7882] = "Frigost is overflowing with talented craftsmen but what we really need is tools. Mac Gayver has told me about a project to make steam-powered blowtorches, more efficient and less exhausting than the traditional ice saws which they use to cut the ice on the lake. The problem is getting the necessary materials to make them.\nI have some lists of the tools and materials needed on me. Would you be able to get them for me? I\'ll pay handsomely in exchange.";
D.q[7883] = "I thank you for your help and pray to Sadida to watch over you. Thanks to these tools, our dream will become a reality much sooner than we\'d hoped.\nMac Gayver is going to be overjoyed when he learns what you\'ve done for us. You should go and see him.";
D.q[7899] = "Herr Peece is a very good doctor, we\'re lucky to have him. He was already a veteran of medicine when I was working on the construction of the Count\'s invention. Like on all big building sites, we had our share of accidents, but no-one ever complained about the treatment provided by Herr Peece.\nNevertheless, you have to admit that his behaviour has changed since the big freeze. In my opinion, he struggled to cope with the deaths of so many people, whether it was the cold, the famine, the island\'s creatures or something else which killed them...\nI\'m going to go and get these vaccines distributed, thanks for your help.";
D.q[7900] = "Word has reached me that you are particularly gifted at finding people who have disappeared. Would you like to find someone for me?\n It\'s my father, Kack Handed. He hasn\'t exactly disappeared, no. In fact, he died about fifty years ago trying to reach the continent via Alma\'s Cradle, on the north-eastern coast of the island. The water there isn\'t frozen but strong tidal currents push the boats onto the reefs.\nI\'m giving you the details of this, oh, so passionate story, because what I would like is for you to find his soul. Haven\'t I told you? This place is haunted by ghost pirates. So, I\'m asking you to go there, find my father and ask him where he has hidden his booty, the fruit of a long life of all kinds of petty crime.";
D.q[6473] = "And that surprises you? Only a mother could love your face... and that pickle in your pants... what exactly were you expecting?";
D.q[747] = "To weaken Brakmar\'s economy we\'ve decided to attack them without respite. Every militiaman will have to bring me 10 Brakmarian badges to prove me their value in battle!";
D.q[7907] = "There\'s still plenty left. You\'re going to be able to make several trips.\nWatch out for the creatures who lurk around here, all the same. Some of them are just waiting for the chance to rip out your guts and gobble you up.";
D.q[7924] = "What list was it again? Oh yes, Emi\'s one. I will probably need you later on, but we can talk about again, in peace and quiet. I\'m a bit overwhelmed at the moment... and the walls have ears.";
D.q[5014] = "Wow, he looks so mad! What he needs is a little rest and relaxation. A little yago would do him the world of good.";
D.q[5269] = "";
D.q[7139] = "";
D.q[5072] = "The Rasputin cake? I\'m the one who make it. \nI swear there was no poison in it. I wanted to bring it to Amayiro but he wasn\'t there so I left it for him. Someone must have replaced it with a Poisoned Raputin cake before he came back. Torche can confirm all this, he went down to ask for a snack just afterwards.";
D.q[5315] = "";
D.q[3495] = "Zog Zog to you.";
D.q[6467] = "Documents on our merchandise convoys, information on prisoners and important citizens, all that means nothing to me. You\'ve done your work well, but watch out, I can\'t guarantee you\'ll be safe outside the walls of this building. It seems that some important people are implicated in this affair.";
D.q[5075] = "Yes, I was on duty at the time. I didn\'t see or hear a thing after the cook went by... I didn\'t even hear anything before he went by actually.";
D.q[841] = "HMM?";
D.q[5358] = "";
D.q[5313] = "";
D.q[6477] = "You bring me this pittance and you\'re still pulling a face... that\'s a great attitude. I\'m not grateful. Not at all.";
D.q[5125] = "Can\'t do a thing, Rogue Inkgo won\'t say a word. Go and see  Merlinmagus Ambrosius at the alchemists workshop and ask him tp prepare some Truth Serum. Then this cursed Rogue will have to confess everything.";
D.q[7295] = "";
D.q[5010] = "";
D.q[1074] = "hmm?";
D.q[1131] = "Ha! Someone with half a brain at last!";
D.q[7418] = "";
D.q[1670] = "Thank you #1! Hyoactive rats are a real nuisance for the productivity of our city. Their Hyoactivity makes people take leave and go have fun at the Trool Fair!";
D.q[1295] = "Ha-ha, I\'ve defeated a militiaman!\nMy uncle will be so proud when he finds out.";
D.q[5160] = "Brave Amayiro told you that I needed your services, then. Before telling you what it\'s all about you must know that this task is of the highest importance. What I want to to do is to find an artefact that was lost when Djaul captured Jiva in the year 132. Another thing, Djaul will do anything to kill the wise protector and this time he would have succeeded if it hadn\'t been for Ulgrude\'s enraged rescue. Djaul was beaten off, for the moment.";
D.q[5951] = "";
D.q[5197] = "";
D.q[6081] = "";
D.q[3233] = "Haha! You arre almost as imprrressive as I used to be when I was yourrr age!";
D.q[5937] = "";
D.q[6077] = "";
D.q[5949] = "";
D.q[7422] = "";
D.q[7423] = "";
D.q[5541] = "Praise be to Silvosse! Praise to the little Dreggon that he taught to fly. I am eternally greatful and I am certain that the Goddess Cra has taken notice of your actions. \nI can teach you no more. It\'s time you take your first steps in Bonta alone.";
D.q[5539] = "Praise be to Silvosse! Praise to the little Dreggon that he taught to fly. I am eternally greatful and I am certain that the Goddess Eniripsa has taken notice of your actions. \nI can teach you no more. It\'s time you take your first steps in Bonta alone.";
D.q[5543] = "Praise be to Silvosse! Praise to the little Dreggon that he taught to fly. I am eternally greatful and I am certain that the Goddess Sacrier has taken notice of your actions. \nI can teach you no more. It\'s time you take your first steps in Bonta alone.";
D.q[5540] = "Praise be to Silvosse! Praise to the little Dreggon that he taught to fly. I am eternally greatful and I am certain that the God Iop has taken notice of your actions. \nI can teach you no more. It\'s time you take your first steps in Bonta alone.";
D.q[5542] = "Praise be to Silvosse! Praise to the little Dreggon that he taught to fly. I am eternally greatful and I am certain that the God Sadida has taken notice of your actions. \nI can teach you no more. It\'s time you take your first steps in Bonta alone.";
D.q[2992] = "To create a party, click on the character that you wish to invite then click on Invite in my Party. Unlike guilds, parties are temporary. Members of the same party have a special channel reserved for their only use and can therefore locate each other a lot easier with the compass.";
D.q[7393] = "";
D.q[5510] = "Great to see you! The Brakmarians are getting more and more violent, but happily Bonta can count on valiant fellows like yourself. \nSilvosse is watching over you.";
D.q[5957] = "Greetings, I\'ve heard that Brakmar has seen much trouble these past days. I think they are still plotting something unpleasant. \nAnd you, how is your research going?";
D.q[3295] = "That\'s right, young Bontarian! After all these years offering our services to great Bonta for nothing, we\'ve finally made it!";
D.q[2915] = "Greetings. I hope you\'ve booted a few Brakmarians around!\nWhat can I do for you?";
D.q[5950] = "Greeting, young assassin. Has the region of Amakna seen much strife of late?";
D.q[6037] = "";
D.q[751] = "A new race of rats has appeared in the sewers of our town. You can easily recognize them because of their green colour and their nasty smell...\nTo fight against the spread of these beasts, we\'ve asked each soldier to kill 4 of them. Now you know what to do #1...";
D.q[1519] = "Do you have an answer to give me?";
D.q[6118] = "You have shown initiative here. In time, your actions will prove important to our Order. I believe you deserve a promotion to Master of illusions considering all you\'ve done.\nCongratulations!";
D.q[5953] = "";
D.q[5958] = "";
D.q[6352] = "Haha. The Bontarians don\'t stand a chance against my cavalry without weapons. We\'re gonna thraaaaaaash them!\nKeep displaying your loyalty to Brakmar like this and maybe you can become a true Bontarian crusher like me.";
D.q[4389] = "It seems like someone wanted to lay the blame on you. I\'ll put this report somewhere safe. That way, if you\'re in trouble, Ture Inge can always produce it to prove that the allegations against you were false. As for you, go get some rest while I decide how we\'re going to sort this problem out";
D.q[7421] = "";
D.q[5707] = "...";
D.q[4647] = "Aaargh... damn you Oto, leaving me to die like this!\nHere, take the bloody documents and get out of here, I\'ll try to hide...";
D.q[6858] = "";
D.q[5706] = "";
D.q[1628] = "HEY BUDDY STOP RIGHT THERE! Where do you think you\'re going?! No way you\'ll get near my children. I don\'t want a weak little pacifist like you teaching them bad habits. They must be surrounded by good, strong men at all times for them to become strong and good themselves!";
D.q[6650] = "";
D.q[7078] = "";
D.q[7092] = "";
D.q[5115] = "Pnj(1011) et Message(5114)";
D.q[7467] = "The second power allows you to reset your characteristics to 101, if you don\'t want to lose anything you\'ve gained through scrolls.\nIf you use it, any characteristic above the value 101 will be reset to 101, and you\'ll get back the appropriate number of characteristic points. A characteristic below the value 101 will not be affected.";
D.q[7099] = "";
D.q[6688] = "";
D.q[6677] = "";
D.q[7088] = "";
D.q[6860] = "";
D.q[6678] = "";
D.q[6682] = "";
D.q[7079] = "";
D.q[6868] = "";
D.q[7089] = "";
D.q[4688] = "";
D.q[4733] = "";
D.q[5714] = "";
D.q[6618] = "";
D.q[4132] = "Watch out! Last time I took him to this island, about 35 years ago, I told him to wait for me and that I\'d be back within a couple of days. I haven\'t come back ever since. I was too glad to get rid of him. He must be extremely mad at me for spending the last 35 years on this desert island with pirates and Kokokos waiting for me to return. It must be worse than spending a lifetime with you! \nAnd while I\'m at it, I\'m really thirsty. Without a drink I won\'t be able to fix the ship\'s sail and hull. Get me a Kokonut and something to drink its juice. And be careful, this time don\'t bring me back rotten food... \nWhat are you waiting for? Hurry up! I\'m parched!";
D.q[7704] = "Blimey, you don\'t look very well at all! Make an appointment with Herr Peece, our doctor, as soon as you can.";
D.q[4722] = "";
D.q[4466] = "Hahaha, you better be joking... haha. You\'re not? Listen, I don\'t know what you have in that block of yours, but I don\'t stick my nose in your business.";
D.q[5743] = "";
D.q[4771] = "";
D.q[5802] = "Greetings. To what do I owe the pleasure?";
D.q[7093] = "";
D.q[5763] = "";
D.q[6330] = "Hahaha. At least you have a sense of humour. That\'s a rare quality in this day and age... most people don\'t even understand what it is.";
D.q[7703] = "Hello, I see that despite my advice, you\'ve fallen ill. If you\'d have listened to me it wouldn\'t have happened.\nGo and see Herr Peece, our doctor, he\'s working on an antidote.";
D.q[5708] = "";
D.q[4165] = "So, did you find her? What did she tell you?";
D.q[6295] = "Hahahahaha, you think we\'re going to obey you just because you found our hideout? \nHahahahaha... you\'re as ridiculous as the ridiculous hat you\'re wearing on your head.";
D.q[4742] = "";
D.q[6628] = "";
D.q[1025] = "I\'ve a feeling that nothing can resist you... Really good, you\'re going up in my esteem, #1.";
D.q[7094] = "";
D.q[7705] = "Buy my Icefish!\nBuy my fresh Icefish!";
D.q[4741] = "You have the Hammer Hitocracy, don\'t you? I can reduce its demonic power if you like. That won\'t make any difference to the power of the blade, but its effects on the possessor of the hammer will be less.";
D.q[6483] = "Halt! Who goes there?";
D.q[5173] = "";
D.q[7095] = "";
D.q[7085] = "";
D.q[1121] = "Get out of my way, creep. I can\'t play with you, I\'ve to calm my brother down.";
D.q[1477] = "Hang on a sec... Here is a Sniffling Staff! You point it at someone and you use it. It works from a distance of 20 meters. Come back again if you need some more.";
D.q[443] = "To take revenge on that monstrous creature, I\'ll never forget it...\nOnce you\'ve killed it, take an Ancestral Amber and try to forge Ancestral Daggers out of it.\n\nThen bring me back these daggers and I\'ll give you Ancestral wood in exchange. Ancestral wood is used in the manufacture of a famous Amulet with dazzling powers or even in the restoration of the legendary Splitter of Ancestral Treechnid, an axe that will make its holder one of the most powerful warriors in Amakna.\nBut be careful, You\'ll have to find a very experienced Dagger Smith to forge the daggers that I\'m looking for. And to manufacture this amulet I\'m talking about or to forge this famous axe, you\'ll have to ask outstanding craftsmen.\nOne last thing, don\'t underestimate the power of that Ancestral Treechnid...";
D.q[7090] = "";
D.q[7091] = "";
D.q[1998] = "Time for a snooze now... *yawns*";
D.q[7673] = "The stock of Apewicubes has to be monitored day and night because Pingwins regularly try to steal them. It is a thankless but necessary task as cutting and assembling all these blocks of ice has already taken a lot of effort.";
D.q[3335] = "When you\'re stronger, you\'ll be able to bring me back some supplies from the Koalak region.";
D.q[7688] = "Your hands are covered with the same blood that is reflected in your eyes.\nHere\'s a little something for your trouble, and if you want to kill other pests, I will always have work for you.";
D.q[7076] = "";
D.q[7329] = "";
D.q[7742] = "Hello, and welcome.\nThe following services are currently available upstairs:\n- Consult a list of all available craftspeople, of every profession.\n- Estate agency, listing the houses and paddocks for sale.\nMassage sessions are reserved for the agency manager and the Militia Chief.";
D.q[3579] = "*Hums*\nGobriel, they consume your soul\nTheir hatred strangles your life\nAnd Bonta, is like a new hope\nSince in their hands you die every night!";
D.q[7674] = "Are you talking about Apewicubes? They contain what was in the lake at the time of freezing, which is to say a bit of everything and anything. Frozen fish, frozen bread, candy, keys, and a bunch of other junk. Once, we even found a breeding item in the ice, would you credit it!";
D.q[7689] = "I have enough people to hunt the creatures lurking around the building. On the other hand, volunteers for the remote areas of the island are rare.\nI immediately saw that we shared a visceral hatred for the creatures on the island.\nHere is the list of animals to kill and most importantly, do not forget to bring me proof of your work.";
D.q[3586] = "Me think situation and me accept it.";
D.q[1145] = "Argh, I didn\'t ask you to bring me back a tooth... are you trying to brown me off?";
D.q[7263] = "";
D.q[5213] = "Good, good. We\'re going condition him well, and then he\'ll be ready for battle.";
D.q[1379] = "Interruptions... blablabla... Magic flux... blablabla... Ah! Here it is! No major risk to Brakmar. That\'s all I wanted to know. The rest is all for the scientists!\nYou see while you were hanging around in the caves, a Bontarian spy unit got into Brakmar! We caught all except one. Plus, he managed to run away with important documents! Catch him and get the documents back... right now! Don\'t hesitate to ask guards and sentinels if they\'ve seen him.";
D.q[7675] = "Oh, a Vibrating Pingwin Feather! What\'s it doing in your arse? Don\'t answer, I don\'t want to know. You probably don\'t know how to use it, right? So much the better... I\'ll swap you one of our freshly cut Apewicubes for it. What say you?";
D.q[7744] = "So there we go, are you familiar with the area?\nFeel free to discuss with the inhabitants of the village and the surrounding area, they have lots of problems to solve.\nWhen you feel up to the task, you can confront Count Harebourg and pocket a portion of his wealth.";
D.q[5355] = "";
D.q[5341] = "It\'s still not perfect. I\'m going to try a new potion on him - I need one unit of Bouftou Blood, 10 Magical Cures, 10 Hemps, and 2 Kaliptus Flowers. I\'ll also need you to report some things you ask my colleagues in the breeders village, on Otomai Island. I can\'t seem to remember his name, though.";
D.q[5293] = "";
D.q[5554] = "That\'s great news! Now that the cereals are growing quicker, we\'ll have plenty of food for the Dragoturkeys. We could even try the same technique for the cereals we feed the troops with. Well, congratulations, I pronounce you a Squire of the realm.";
D.q[7676] = "Thank you. Here, take any of these Apewicubes.\nIf you find other Vibrating Pingwin Feathers, don\'t hesitate to come swap them for more Apewicubes, I have a stock of them since you helped us rebuild our fishing lines.";
D.q[2717] = "Don\'t deny it! I know you brought one of those damned Dofus onto our island! We saw you leaving the Shaman\'s house! You broke the first Pandikaze rule: No Dofus on Pandala. I sentence you to poisoning by Pandneken! You\'ll be executed tomorrow. Imprison the... the... crook. Good night!";
D.q[7691] = "The town hall is located near the Zaap, recently repaired thanks to mainlanders.\nLook, here\'s a map, I\'ve indicated the area\'s important points.";
D.q[7272] = "";
D.q[5348] = "";
D.q[1239] = "Hum ho... I need a pair of shoes...";
D.q[1972] = "Want another compromise?";
D.q[5074] = "This is the first time I\'ve seen a treason case resolved so quickly. It must be said that you have conducted your investigation well.";
D.q[7677] = "Take your time and let me know when you\'ve decided.";
D.q[7687] = "I saw the red glow in your eyes. You hate animals too, don\'t you.\nHere\'s the list of animals to kill and most importantly, don\'t forget to bring me proof of your work.";
D.q[7692] = "Hello and welcome to Frigost.\nAs you could see on your way over here, the village is not at its best, but thanks to the efforts of our brave citizens, contact has been restored with the mainland.";
D.q[2183] = "Has Locette woken up? Good, I was afraid she would die if she spent one more night without her senses. You can\'t imagine how important each of them is to the very essence of life. Regarding the sense disorder, we carry on with the ancestral remedies. Go at the far end of the western cave and pick up a stone. Bring it as fast as you can to Shani, the jeweller, she will tell you why it needs to be quick.";
D.q[7336] = "";
D.q[7254] = "";
D.q[5249] = "Ha, an earring is it? Interesting... I have an idea who\'s guilty, but I\'m not totally sure... hmm, how can we confirm my suspicion? Ah, I know. Go find dear Divad in the tower - his top notch guesswork will be useful. Ask him who owns this earring.";
D.q[1287] = "Drink to Brakmar! The best city in the world! I shall serve my city till I die!";
D.q[2535] = "Our goddess thanks you through my words: this Dofus is a very good copy! Grandapan admires adventurers like you, those brave souls who are ready to put their lives at stake for the precious dragon eggs. Ask Grandapan anything you like...";
D.q[4864] = "";
D.q[7338] = "";
D.q[7218] = "";
D.q[4832] = "";
D.q[5559] = "Have you found out what Brakmarians have behind their heads?";
D.q[7335] = "";
D.q[5106] = "Have you found a solution? I really hope so!";
D.q[4623] = "Our recent failures are getting up my nose. However, I think I\'ve found a way to crush Bonta once and for all. We\'re going to find the powerful magic horn you were told about at Madrestam Harbour. Head over to the Ripate Inn and find out more about it.";
D.q[4515] = "Have you calmed Lenglad down?";
D.q[5701] = "Have you gone nuts? Just look at this ring...";
D.q[3227] = "In spite of appearances, Porcos are extremely religious creatures and the cult of the Dragon Pig is widespread among the Porcos! There\'s also Ougah, a minor divinity with a Mush for a head. My granddad used to say he didn\'t believe in Ougaa but that the deity then came and scared the living daylights out of him...\nWell, I must confess that I believe in Ougah and the only thing that scares me is the Dragon Pig! And yet, Ougah is a great man, mate!";
D.q[7686] = "Thank you for avenging the affront caused to my wife by the Royal Mastogob. I\'ll tell my friend from the Ego Flagship Company to let you use his carrier.";
D.q[4290] = "Ooh? O lovely jewel. But of course, I\'ve ten or more on me right now. Here, take whichever one you like... on the house!";
D.q[1107] = "Raaaah! My horn! Where is my hooooorn!";
D.q[7709] = "If you want to learn more about the area, the easiest way is to meet with residents of the village.\nObviously, it is useless to talk to them all, so I\'ve prepared a list of the most interesting ones.\nWhen you\'re familiar with the area, come see me, I have several things I\'d like you to do for me.";
D.q[5300] = "";
D.q[7322] = "";
D.q[7266] = "";
D.q[4056] = "Despite your doubtful appearance and your silly smile, I knew you were respectable!\nWell, it\'s pretty easy. I\'m looking for any type of mount: ginger, green, shaved, hairy, foul-smelling, immature, sterile... All types of mounts interest me as long as they\'re alive. Hahahahah!\nBring me mount certificates and I\'ll give you scrolls I found in the library in exchange. You can even bring me invalid certificates. I\'ll manage to falsify them.";
D.q[7269] = "";
D.q[7217] = "";
D.q[5372] = "";
D.q[4230] = "A special technique is required for this mysterious bacteria. We suspect that it may have appeared shortly after the world was created, in the time when the subtleties of all the elements were known to man.";
D.q[7748] = "Whilst we were experimenting with cereals, I came up with the idea of modifying them so they could be used in different types of food to increase their profitability, for example, by making biscuits. For this, I need 60 Granola Seeds, which the creatures of the Lonsome Pine Trails are particularly fond of. I also need ten Pynekone Seeds to study their exceptional resistance to cold. Can you take care of that?";
D.q[3448] = "Have you got the recipe or what? Good! Go and look for the ingredients and I\'ll cook them.";
D.q[2533] = "Have you noticed that you always repeat the ends of my sentences... Weird habit you have... Oh well! The ancestors of the Pandawa used to be robust fellows. Bottle-fed since their childhood with fermented bamboo milk, our forebears used to learn the three commandments off by heart from a young age.";
D.q[5071] = "";
D.q[5194] = "Here you are again! I have a new mission for you. We have reason to believe that Ronan the Barbarian has just been captured by a Bontarian convoy. I want you to intercept this convoy and to bring Ronan here - he could be very useful to us down the line.";
D.q[7690] = "Hello, welcome to the village of Frigost. Do you have a good trip?\nI haven\'t seen a flowery shirt or shorts for a long time, but you should cover up more, or you may catch the Lurgi. If you haven\'t already, I invite you to meet our mayor, she will be happy to welcome you and show you around the different areas.";
D.q[4359] = "Haven\'t seen any Ecaflips, but last night I heard the guards talking about a group of Ecaflips who were creating problems lately. Maybe that will help you...";
D.q[7749] = "Herr Peece told me that Pingwins are very resilient because they eat grains rich in iron. Perhaps we can use that information to make our cereals more resilient too.\nBring me 65 Lentil Seeds and I will reward you further.";
D.q[660] = "You\'ll come across many closed doors on your path, young one. Some of them should remain closed since they hide dangerous creatures, but some others could make you rich and valiant... just knock at the right ones! \n\nThe door behind me is a training dungeon. I put some Gobball flocks in there. If you want to enter it, you\'ll have to find the key. I hid it on one of their fellow creatures.";
D.q[764] = "Be part of a jury";
D.q[1554] = "Fantastic, I knew you would be up to the task! Take this Bwak Egg as a reward. Personally I use it in potions, but feel free to find out what else it can do.";
D.q[7594] = "What you see over there are the treasures of a lifetime spent hunting and adventuring, and that\'s only the half of it. \nWhen you too have lived through as many adventures as I have, you\'ll want to settle down as well, and that\'s when the boredom will set in. \nI was a member of the Rogues, defeated the Mega Crackler one on one and beat the Irascible Dragnoute in a flat race. I witnessed the capture of the demon As\'Ruoy\'Dnim, who terrorised Amakna, I discovered the island of Otomai with my friend Captain Kradoc and I even travelled to Kwismas Island and met Count Harebourg himself.";
D.q[7253] = "";
D.q[5221] = "I want you to go and see Kalfen, an old member of the Triumvirate who... luckily... found his way to the hideout. Make him an offer - I can set him free if he agrees to launch a propaganda campaign for Djaul in his order... the Order of the Unsound Mind.";
D.q[5314] = "";
D.q[1186] = "This tower? It\'s the meeting point of the three most powerful orders in Bonta: the Order of the Sharp Eye, the Order of the Salvatory Spirit and the Order of the Valiant Heart.";
D.q[4011] = "Yes, you\'ve proven your strength... Alright, I\'ll serve your prince.";
D.q[1177] = "Greetings dear disciple of Menalt, I see you\'re tougher than when we last met! \nWhat can I do for you?";
D.q[7750] = "";
D.q[5012] = "He didn\'t understand the first time or what?";
D.q[4459] = "Oto Mustam sent me here. I\'ve to turn the Bonta militia into the worst fighting force possible.";
D.q[2059] = "Whadya want?";
D.q[2144] = "Ohh, this is not cool... Wait, make an effort, man... Bring me the extract of Dizbi flower so that I can quietly smell it while I contemplate nature around my favourite chest-nut tree.";
D.q[7710] = "Thank you, it\'s not much but it will help us a lot. It\'s not like it used to be, that\'s for sure. I still remember the long lines of carts filled with grain that were shuttling between the fields and the port... Anyway, that belongs to the past, no need to go over it all again.";
D.q[3955] = "Oh, that dear Uba... Give him this scroll. I think it will help him.";
D.q[2643] = "AAAAAHHHH! Go away! Go away! Go away! Go away!";
D.q[4592] = "He shouldn\'t go too quickly in his condition, but don\'t hang around nevertheless. Another Brakmarian may find him and take the documents.";
D.q[7694] = "Ah, I\'d like that a lot. Bea Fortax usually gets my cereal for me, but she\'s a bit of a daydreamer and often forgets to turn up for work. I\'ve tried several times to reason with her but what can you do? She\'s a Sadida, and you can\'t fight against the nature of things. Us Frigostians are well placed to know that. In short, it would be great if you could take her place and bring me a dozen Frosteez.";
D.q[1526] = "What on earth are you talking about? You have not met him yet. Are you kidding me?";
D.q[3915] = "Have I seen any nobles? I sure have. A few of them at once, if you can believe it. Let me tell you, they\'re not so noble when I\'m kicking them out the back door in the early hours of the morning!";
D.q[3042] = "Rargh! I feel weak! I don\'t have much energy left!";
D.q[7753] = "Thank you, with your help we can continue our experiments on cereals and who knows, maybe one day we will revive our agriculture sufficiently enough to be able to compete with Amakna once more.";
D.q[7226] = "";
D.q[5274] = "";
D.q[5853] = "Ah, you\'re back. I was wondering what happened. Did anything strange happen in Amakna while you were there?";
D.q[5100] = "Gobball Slobber, Trool\'s Blood and... Arghhh! You interrupted me JUST at the wrong moment! What do you want?";
D.q[5110] = "Good, good. I\'ll get busy moulding these miserable creatures to my will and turning them into useful guards.";
D.q[7711] = "";
D.q[3615] = "Gobrator stay alone, difficult fate. No energy to live anymore. My heart does not vibrate anymore. Farewell.";
D.q[3620] = "You want feathers? Me trade for Bwork beer.";
D.q[278] = "Hee-hee! Hi there! My name is Mori Arty, I\'m the greatest villain of all time. I got arrested and had to peel potatoes for over ten years. But now I\'m free again, and I\'ll repeat the same thing every night: try to take over the world!";
D.q[5272] = "";
D.q[1913] = "He\'s quitting? I\'m going to fire him before he even has time to quit! Find me a new delivery man! Sorry, but you\'re the only one around...";
D.q[7712] = "No, I\'ve told you, I don\'t want your manure here. I\'m getting rather tired of that stupid joke.\nOh, you\'re not here to deliver manure? But you\'re all crusty, though, I thought... well... no, nothing.\nHold on... you\'re not from round here, obviously!\nForget all that about manure, and welcome to my studio.\nWould you like a little tea?";
D.q[2623] = "Grimph\n*He\'s pretending to nibble at a bamboo that\'s lying on the ground.*";
D.q[4978] = "";
D.q[5076] = "The Wabbits dug so much that they found an underground tunnel. I sense a devilish presence deep within, but it may just be a trap. You\'re going to go in first to test the water, then come back with a full report once you\'ve reached the end.";
D.q[7755] = "When I think about the Count\'s invention which should have enabled us to benefit from longer growth cycles by allowing the crops to survive hard, but short winters... winter is here for good and now our abundant crops are only a distant memory.\nDo you have any lentil seeds? Thanks. By crossbreeding these with other cereals we should be able to obtain new, more resistant species.";
D.q[7713] = "";
D.q[486] = "Heheheh, these secret missions are for the clan masters only.";
D.q[4193] = "Otomai wanted to bring two of each creature he knew across to this island. Then he wanted to breed, or even cross-breed them, and study the evolution of the hybrids he created. But to be able to carry out such experiments, he needed large quantities of alchemy equipment, and of course, food. \nThat\'s why I made the journey so often. \nSince sea cartography can be extremely inaccurate, we often made unscheduled detours to Moon Island or Castaway Island.";
D.q[5389] = "";
D.q[5896] = "";
D.q[2645] = "Heitit? Hum... at this time of the day, he must be either practising at the Dojo or looking for food.";
D.q[2366] = "There\'s some pretty big monsters over there... Even my granddaddy never heard of them, they\'d scare a lop they would! And then there\'s all those old legends.";
D.q[7756] = "";
D.q[4238] = "Otomai\'s secret is well guarded. This last creation, cultivated from the most potent bacterial strains on the island, consumes everything in its path. The trans-dimensional nature of the Plasmogrine allows this creature to place its stomach in another dimension. What is more, it\'s quasi-immortal!";
D.q[7757] = "";
D.q[4895] = "Visit the following temples and see if they know anything: Cra, Ecaflip, Eniripsa, Feca, Iop and Sacrier. Be sure to ask all of the Temple Masters, it is very important that nothing escapes our attention.";
D.q[5517] = "What can I do for you, Brakmarian?";
D.q[7715] = "";
D.q[7758] = "";
D.q[3990] = "By the good gods, what was that monstew? My couwage pwevailed ovew its cwuelty. This won\'t stop my quest, I\'ve got a pwincess to mawwy! You must become stwongew if you want to follow me.";
D.q[5105] = "BONTARIANS!? That makes me mad! If they\'ve already dirtied the temple, they might find my lair... and I don\'t think I\'m in the mood to slaughter them right now...\nHum, the problem is that no one wants to guard such a deserted area. Go to Brakmar and bring me some guards.";
D.q[5809] = "";
D.q[1701] = "Hello #! What can I do for you?";
D.q[7759] = "In the past, agriculture flourished because the soil of the island, composed of volcanic dust, is very rich in minerals.\nThe only obstacle was the winter, very short but incredibly intense. So intense that it broke the crop cycle and forced us to sow, grow and harvest the crop only during the temperate periods. All crops sown before the winter were destroyed during the winter.";
D.q[5597] = "Poppy Seeds? Interesting... and you say he needs 20? I think I\'ve an idea... we\'ll replace the Poppy seeds with Scurvion seeds. If this Merlinmagus fellow is as useless as Finche Aticus says he is, he won\'t realise a thing! I\'ve 20 freshly picked Scurvion seeds on me right now. I\'ll soak them in strong poison and change their appearance using Magic Greenish Dye. Go get me everything I need. And be quick.";
D.q[1352] = "*Scissors*\nHem, I lost. You\'re pretty good... Let\'s play the third round.";
D.q[7716] = "";
D.q[523] = "Well, well, well! It looks like my wish has been granted, I\'m not alone anymore! Welcome to Moon Island, roomie! I\'m Gropinson Cruaule. Have I already introduced myself? I can\'t remember. There have been so many new arrivals lately, hahaha!";
D.q[6754] = "Watch out. Oshima doesn\'t allow some types of soul into his sanctuary. You may enter if you clothe yourself in the ethereal envelope of a ghost. By fighting some of the creatures in the sanctuary you\'ll certainly gain Oshima\'s favour. What form would you like to take when you enter the sanctuary?";
D.q[1353] = "*Rock*\nEhh, I lost. You\'re pretty good... Let\'s play the third round.";
D.q[7714] = "I don\'t have the time!\nDrink a good litre of alcohol, immerse the wound in hot water and dress it with a bandage that has been sterilized beforehand with Mastogob slobber.\nEh, what, you\'re not hurt?\nOh, sorry, what I can do for you? Hurry, I don\'t have much time to give you because at the rate the Lurgi is spreading, there\'ll be an epidemic soon. I must find an effective vaccine before it is too late.";
D.q[6034] = "";
D.q[2496] = "Perfect! Go see one of our famous peddlers! They\'re enlisted by the Grandapan to receive the tax payment and will be happy to take a few Kamas off you. Hurrah for Pandala! Long live the Grandapan!";
D.q[4901] = "A Hammer of Light, or a light hammer? You need to speak more clearly, as I don\'t understand a single word of your gibberish.";
D.q[7760] = "Well, I wasn\'t expecting that! It is rare to see men of good will today. \nI need fresh Mastogob blood samples. Go into the fields and take a half-dozen. \nMind you, I only want samples taken from sick adult Mastogobs, but not too old, nor too young.";
D.q[4206] = "Climbing so high and still being alive is quite a feat. I suppose you feel ready to confront the master, the incredible Kimbo. He\'s the keeper of this tree, and is respected by all the creatures on the island. He was here long before Otomai even arrived to carry out all his experiments and until now, those who defied him have been humiliated.\nThis creature loves to toy with naive adventurers, and he has boundless treachery. That\'s why Otomai loves him so much!";
D.q[5745] = "";
D.q[7718] = "";
D.q[7719] = "Hello you, you\'re looking for fresh fish, aren\'t you? You\'re in luck, mine is the freshest, whatever the time of year. The same can\'t be said for that poor Lucette , but them\'s the breaks, love. You don\'t have to believe me if you won\'t want to, but I saw Mac Gayver fooling around with little Mel. What would her mother say if she knew...";
D.q[6905] = "Mouahahahah. Just a little longer and I can finally get out of here.\nHuh? What? Who dares to disturb me?\nWho are you and what are you doing here?\nAre you going to challenge me, or are you just here to offer yourself up for sacrifice?";
D.q[982] = "Hello #1. Amayiro sent you to bring me Gobball teeth, am I right?";
D.q[5525] = "Ho, yes. Thanks to you I\'ll get a nice little extension on my Bontarian villa. Good luck kid.";
D.q[5282] = "";
D.q[5749] = "You really think I have nothing else to do? Here, I\'ll note the recipe on a piece of paper for you to deal with yourself, and if you\'re not a fishmonger or an alchemist, find someone else to prepare your seeds.";
D.q[7720] = "My family have been animal trainers for five generations. The big freeze has allowed me to perfect my skills and I am currently the best Bow Wow trainer in the history of Frigost. No matter what anyone tells you, it was me who trained them all. Yes, I\'m still talking about the Bow Wows. The key to successful training is to take a firm stance and any snow Bow Wow owners will tell you the same thing.\nDon\'t get me wrong, my training talents can be used on almost all the creatures in Frigost, the Bow Wows are just my speciality.";
D.q[2969] = "What do I know? I\'m not a Tofu breeder!";
D.q[3137] = "Perfect! It\'s incredible! My dream has finally come true! I\'ll never be as charismatic as the Koolich! \nYou really deserve this key I\'ve just given you. But remember, Skeunk is an Eniripsa Master and he\'s very dangerous. For what I know, no one has ever defeated him!\nTo find Skeunk, you\'ll have to cross an arid valley filled with dangerous Koalaks and once there, you\'ll have to show this key to the guard of Skeunk\'s hideout...";
D.q[5390] = "";
D.q[5095] = "";
D.q[2198] = "Perfect. Here we are, ahahah! Ahem! Excuse me! Very well, let\'s have a look... *Kwartzwatch focuses on the flow of Epyss, then is overcome by bolts of lightning, and she drops the hourglass, which breaks* By the Twelve! What was that vision? Let me come back to my senses. May Xelor have mercy, I fear the worst...";
D.q[5365] = "";
D.q[7361] = "";
D.q[7721] = "";
D.q[5766] = "You\'re doing well, certain disreputable inns are buzzing with stories of your exploits. It\'ll cost you 2,000 Kamas to switch. \nAnd don\'t forget, you can join the weaker alignment for free!";
D.q[5398] = "";
D.q[7470] = "";
D.q[7471] = "";
D.q[6443] = "Hello and welcome to Bagrutte\'s Inn. You\'ll find everything you need to refresh yourself here. My name is Ecaline, and I\'ll be your exclusive waitress for as long as you stay with us... if you want me to be, that is. Rrrrrr.";
D.q[1911] = "Pooh! I\'ve a date but things aren\'t going too smoothly. I\'m sick too. And just look at my skin, I didn\'t get enough sleep. I\'ve to try and get some rest. I can\'t do any deliveries today. I\'m sorry.";
D.q[5770] = "Talk of you has crossed your town\'s walls and spreads far and wide! I\'m happy for you kid, but it makes it harder to convert you to neutral. I\'ll need 32,000 Kamas.\nAnd don\'t forget, you can join the weaker alignment for free!";
D.q[3254] = "Pheeeew.... It\'s way tooo \'ot in \'ere...\nYou\'re never annoyed by the sun? The \'eat? \n\n*streaming with sweat*\n\nHmm, I wanna to go back to my island...";
D.q[3614] = "Pinkgob no come. I angry! Kill favourite Piwis and she come for sure!";
D.q[7723] = "";
D.q[5768] = "Your star is rising fast, you\'re messing with the big boys now. It\'ll cost you 8,000 Kamas to go neutral.\nAnd don\'t forget, you can join the weaker alignment for free!";
D.q[5967] = "What do conflicts matter so long as everyone blooms in the way they choose?";
D.q[5764] = "You\'re young, weak and unimportant. It will only cost you 500 Kamas to regain your neutrality. \nAnd don\'t forget, you can join the weaker alignment for free!";
D.q[34] = "Hello matey!\nI need a few ingredients to make my bread rolls taste a bit better. If you bring me a cawwot, I\'ll give you a salt sachet as a reward.";
D.q[5281] = "";
D.q[6422] = "You\'re like a bad smell, you are. Show me your sword.\n...\nI\'ve seen many Ecaflips with this type of sword. The ones who live outside the city walls. I can\'t remember where exactly though - do you think I remember everywhere I go, do you? Speaking of going, didn\'t I ask you to get the hell out of here?";
D.q[5516] = "Hello. No doubt you\'re aware of the increasing violence between the rival cities. Many soldiers have become weary of the constant fighting and have decided to desert the first chance they get. Those who do so are forced to live as fugitives.\nOur good king Allister has taken pity on these souls and is offering them a second chance at a normal life in Amakna. I can help you with the documents you need to declare your neutrality.";
D.q[7724] = "";
D.q[4350] = "Am I not making sense or are you just hard of hearing? I need a militiaman who isn\'t a complete green horn. This creature is an incompetent of the highest order. I can\'t go giving him responsibility for important missions.";
D.q[1333] = "Hem, he makes a perfect culprit but something\'s missing...";
D.q[6773] = "";
D.q[5752] = "";
D.q[4965] = "The Wabbits who arrived have been broken into slaves. The construction of the temple can now begin. Wabbits might not be the most dedicated of workers, but they\'ll have to do for now.";
D.q[4952] = "I want you to find out about these chains that are binding me. Allister, cursed bloody coward, is the one who put me here - search the Castle of Amakna with a fine toothed comb and find a way to get me out of here!";
D.q[2633] = "Hello noble adventurer! Sli Dento bows before you. How may I help you?";
D.q[6287] = "Counsellor Boyowa didn\'t throw you in prison? Sorry, I mean... did everything go well with Counsellor Boyowa? Did you deliver the box of merchandise?";
D.q[2782] = "Psss.... blabla... Psssshh.... fake....Passhh... Dofus.... blab....sshhh\nHuh? Am I talking to myself?";
D.q[6600] = "Hello noble servant of Bonta. Is the mission for the glory of Bonta advancing?";
D.q[5754] = "";
D.q[7362] = "";
D.q[6105] = "Did the Protectors really carry on like you say? You have to wonder who the real bad guys are in this story. \nI think you deserve to join the ranks of the Master of Shadow.\nWhat do you think of that?";
D.q[6106] = "Did the Protectors really carry on like you say? You have to wonder who the real bad guys are in this story. \nI think you deserve to join the ranks of the Masters of Shadows.\nWhat do you think of that?";
D.q[5557] = "Now I just have to remember where I put that recipe...\nWell, it\'s very simple. Put a drop of this potion on each seed and plant them all in the ground. Then just read this scroll aloud... you do know how to read, don\'t you?\nThis spell only works on oats, so make sure you go to the right field! It\'s very important that you follow the instructions to the letter, which is why you\'ll need some farmers and alchemists to help you out. I\'ve sent someone to prepare the field for you and I\'ve marked the place on your map so you won\'t lose any time.";
D.q[7727] = "Damned bugs! If the count hadn\'t betrayed us, my mines would not be infested. I hope that one of these days, someone strong enough will give him what he\'s had coming for a long time. We need the people of Amakna to kick his arse, because the jokers we\'ve had up to now haven\'t done a thing. \nIn the meantime, my mines are infested and there\'s no way to source obsidian.";
D.q[3268] = "Hello super tester!\nI\'m sure you\'d like to test both old and new professions!";
D.q[7349] = "";
D.q[5845] = "";
D.q[5755] = "";
D.q[2179] = "Oh, is it the flower I needed for Locette\'s remedy? Very well, I\'ll prepare the potion now. I must confess that her case is beyond even my talents, I hope it will have an effect... There you go, bring this potion to Yol as fast as your little trotters will carry you.";
D.q[352] = "This sap is almost magic. When correctly used, it can bring a Staff of Treechnid Roots back to life and make it extremely powerful. Ask a high level Staff Carver for more information. A good carver should be able to make it if you bring some of this sap...\nBe careful, this worked sap must be handled with care. It has been worked by a renowned alchemist, Adam Haihaive who transformed himself in an Treechnid for a couple hours to take a sip of the sticky stuff.";
D.q[7348] = "";
D.q[5002] = "";
D.q[7372] = "";
D.q[7728] = "";
D.q[5454] = "Roast Gobball in Kokoko juice! Four Blop Pizza! Great big Tofu kebabs! Abrakebabra! What can I get you?";
D.q[1677] = "Hello there! By the looks of you, you need to let off some steam, get out of your routine. You know, same old thing: Zaap, Craft, Sleep. Well, no need to go any further, I can help you fix all that. Try to win the jackpot! Only 20 Kamas!";
D.q[5856] = "";
D.q[5771] = "Ronan the Barbarian himself trembles upon hearing your name. What I\'m trying to say is that it\'s going to be a lot of trouble to convert you. And you know what that means... I get paid overtime! And you\'ll have to work overtime to pay me! I\'ll make you neutral for 64,000, that\'s the best I can do.\nAnd don\'t forget, you can join the weaker alignment for free!";
D.q[7729] = "";
D.q[5940] = "Hello there. How are ya?";
D.q[5005] = "";
D.q[6469] = "Hello there. So, you\'re in charge of the supplies? You must have done something really stupid to end up here. Unless you\'ve just joined the militia and Amayiro has chosen a particularly nasty initiation task for you! Whatever the case, thanks for the ham!";
D.q[5756] = "Every time I try to do something original, I am accused of trying to imitate Xavier the Baker, when in truth it\'s him who is trying to copy me.";
D.q[7730] = "";
D.q[5370] = "";
D.q[4974] = "Yeah? You want to apologise for the pathetic assassination attempt?";
D.q[5258] = "Several, but I still have to meet some people before I put you on the case. Come back to see me a bit later.";
D.q[5279] = "";
D.q[7731] = "";
D.q[5592] = "Go have a look around Bonta and ask Finche Aticus if he has any news.";
D.q[6249] = "Hello there. What are you doing at my house? If you\'re looking to burgle the place, let me warn you that my uncle Starky is captain of the Bonta militia. He\'ll make you pay if you dare.";
D.q[4948] = "Someone important has asked to see you. They are north-east of here, in the Tower of Gisgoul. You\'ll find an altar there - you have to place a Gobball stomach on it. Then go to the South-East of the room, between the two pillars.";
D.q[2150] = "Hurry up and get yourself to the Blacksmith. He\'ll melt down those Kamas and make a good blade. Follow your compass and come back here when you\'re done.";
D.q[5283] = "";
D.q[3541] = "Hello young Ecaflip. I know that your class is addicted to dangerous adventure. If you really want to bring your life into the bargain, I\'ve got something that\'s right up our street. Are you ready to take some big risks, young one?";
D.q[7732] = "Hi, you know that it\'s thanks to me and my guys that we managed to restore a route to Amakna? Well, not exactly Amakna, but it\'s basically the same.\nWe worked hard for decades to bring the heat to the port and develop a system of steam heating, and it has finally paid off. Now, I need to get the rest of the port thawed out, and I\'m not there yet.";
D.q[3314] = "I want to chaaaaaaaarge! Bring back those Dragoturkeys!";
D.q[5759] = "";
D.q[4605] = "Hurry up. It\'s all written in the orders I gave you.";
D.q[6098] = "";
D.q[7465] = "Hello! I can see you\'ve got a Magical Orb. It has two powers but you can only use one of them. Do you want to find out more about them?";
D.q[7733] = "You know about alchemy? That would explain the condition of your clothes...\nGood, it\'s nice to meet someone with an IQ higher than a Mastogob. I have a little favour to ask, and I\'m asking you, because I can not rely on my fellow citizens. Well, I say \"citizens\", they\'re barely civilised, really.\nThere are so many miscreants around here that I can\'t leave my shop unattended, and my reserves of Snowdrops are dwindling day by day. Can you bring me a dozen?";
D.q[4973] = "What? WHAT?! You dare to criticise my plan? Watch your manner, lowly servant. You\'ll do as I say, and you\'ll do it without saying a thing, ok!\nIf you need help, ask the other idiots in the Tower of Brakmar instead of coming to bother me!";
D.q[6785] = "Shush Tercesasti? He doesn\'t come here anymore ever since his allergic reaction to the Bow Meow and Arachnee hairs, which is a shame, as he was a good customer.";
D.q[6103] = "Greetings, your evil aura is worthy of your cruel heart. What can I do for you?";
D.q[6100] = "Greetings. Such an evil aura cannot pass unfelt. Tell me what  I need to know about the Assmembly of Protectors.";
D.q[986] = "Knock out that wabbit GM, get your sywinge and take a sample of blood fwom it. Simple.\nBwing me the analysis of this blood and I pwomise you a good wewawd.";
D.q[5780] = "Greetings. My name is Nudcan McLoad, from the McLoad clan. I help people in need, it\'s my passion in life, and in these parts, there\'s no shortage of people in need. Some fold have an annoying habit of putting themselves in danger... it\'s bloody amazing.";
D.q[5839] = "Greetings. I suppose you\'re not here just to say hello?";
D.q[4997] = "";
D.q[5243] = "";
D.q[3668] = "More!";
D.q[5241] = "";
D.q[5820] = "";
D.q[4950] = "You have no reason left to be here. Get out of my sight, I have very important meetings to attend.";
D.q[7734] = "Oh, they are so beautiful... Before everything froze over, hundreds of different plant species coexisted on Frigost. But the Frigostians preferred to follow the Count and make fun of me... That will teach those idiots! Speaking of flowers, you should visit our greenhouses, outside of the village. My friends Truffo and Bisale are working on new species. You can\'t miss them, there are several in the fields around the village.";
D.q[7074] = "";
D.q[630] = "Some bones you\'ll find here are just astonishing. Still animated by life of their own years after their death. What a fascinating subject! I could spend my own afterlife on it! Hehehe!";
D.q[1139] = "Quick, efficient, silent... just a few adjectives that don\'t suit you.\n#1, seriously, could have gotten me this pulp any slower?\nAnyway, I\'ve just heard the bloody Tabi has been immunised against common poisons. Only a magical poison will work.";
D.q[35] = "Hello there, stranger.\nI\'m one of Amakna\'s most renowned jewellers. Everybody wants to get their hands on my latest creations.\nAs a consequence, I\'m a bit snowed under with work. So, if you\'re looking for a job, I can definitely give you something to do.";
D.q[7735] = "Olala, do not talk to me about that. With the arrival of all these people from the continent, my reserves are running out before my eyes. I\'m so afraid of not having enough for the next few months that I stopped feeding them to my Bow Meow. Poor little Duss is so hungry.\nHow would you like to make some Kamas? If you bring me 10 Icefish, I will reward you generously.";
D.q[5740] = "";
D.q[5744] = "";
D.q[5366] = "";
D.q[4454] = "50,000 Kamas? For that much money, I\'d come and join you! But it doesn\'t look like you have enough!";
D.q[134] = "Hi, I\'m Grizmine and I live for games of chance. Do you want me to sign you up for the great Raffle of Amakna?\nI\'ve a great game we can play, it\'s called \"The Bottles of Chance\". Or a card game if you prefer. Do you know \"Tragic the Gardening\"?.";
D.q[7736] = "Thank you, if other people were like you, my Icefish reserves would last a good while yet. I heard that Herr Peece, our doctor, contracted a nasty disease in his youth. It even seems that his search for a vaccine against the Lurgi is a pretext to find a cure for his disease. I\'m telling you this because someone I trust told me.";
D.q[5823] = "";
D.q[5122] = "As\'Ruoy\'Dnim named me lieutenant-colonel as soon as I arrived! I mean, I don\'t have any responsibility, but \'lieutenant-colonel Kapp Tenn\' sounds pretty good now doesn\'t it?";
D.q[5860] = "";
D.q[3755] = "Sometimes I feel like I\'m being controlled by a superior entity, like it\'s telling me what to do and what to say. I don\'t think it\'s one of the twelve gods, it\'s something else.";
D.q[4163] = "He sometimes forgets that a relationship needs attention and a little spark to stay alive...\nWhen we lived in Bonta together, we were head over heels in love with each other.\nBut as time passed by, our romance fell asleep and lost the flame that lit our first magic moments.\nThat\'s when he decided to take me on this strange island so that we start a new life, far from the dirty city.";
D.q[7737] = "Why should I trust you? All my staff left when the creatures first appeared in the mines. The Count betrayed me, the Frigostians betrayed me... How could it get any worse? I just need Obsidian to melt the alloys to maintain the piping system that feeds the port. Bring me a dozen.";
D.q[5918] = "An evil little crow? That\'s the taste of a Brakmarian alright. I suppose the black feathers go nicely with Morgan Faym\'n\'s jet black hair. Go to the Astrub Tavern and find a Bontarian spy by the name of Yve Konpetmin - he\'s suceeded in infiltrating the enemy... Now run along and do what you have to do, and let me get on with my business. And don\'t breathe a word about our little arrangement to anyone, ok.";
D.q[5824] = "";
D.q[5645] = "";
D.q[4262] = "";
D.q[4261] = "";
D.q[4251] = "";
D.q[7738] = "You\'re braver than you look. It\'s people like you that we need to settle the score with Count Harebourg.";
D.q[4252] = "";
D.q[246] = "I\'m sorry, but I\'m not going to let you in until you\'re experienced enough to pull out a Karne Rider\'s nails. If I let you in now, you\'ll be torn to pieces.";
D.q[4254] = "";
D.q[5753] = "";
D.q[3674] = "You can tell Qwizitor that everything\'s fine.";
